he snack with a small, pleased expression before placing it between her lips, biting, and chewing. After she tastes it, she glances toward the viewer with a mild, satisfied look.\n\nWhistles are then presented as a serving food. A Whistles package is tipped over a plate already holding a colorful arrangement of food, including leafy greens and small clusters that look like salad or garnish. The tube-shaped snacks tumble from the box onto the plate and scatter around the other food. Another hand dips a Whistle into a round bowl of thick white dip sprinkled with dark herb flecks, pressing the snack into the creamy surface. A stemmed glass dish filled with Whistles appears next; a hand reaches down from above and selects one from the top of the pile.\n\nThe Whistles box returns prominently. The large “SNACK! Whistles” label fills the image, then the package is shown smaller against a pale background. To its right appears bold printed text: “suddenly... snacks are in great shape!” The slogan sits beside the package, with the box on the left and the words stacked vertically on the right. A simplified General Mills “G” logo graphic appears next, set inside a rounded, horn-like emblem.\n\nThe second half shifts to another historical-looking scene. A flat, line-drawn illustration of an antique open car fills the screen, with sketched trees and a countryside background behind it. A real male-presenting actor sits in the driver’s seat, wearing a dark suit and a brimmed hat. He tips his hat with one hand, then settles both hands near the steering wheel. The drawn car has large spoked wheels, an upright windshield, and a horn mounted near the front; pale steam or smoke rises near the hood. The actor looks down into the car, reaches for a tall paper container or bag, and pulls out pieces of snack food. He holds the bag upright in his lap, takes a piece, and brings it to his mouth, chewing while still seated in the illustrated antique car.\n\nAgain, the word “now” appears large on a plain pale background. A wavy line snakes across the screen and becomes another stylized horn graphic, this time suggesting the shape of a bugle. A Bugles package appears. The box has the same strong graphic style: a top band reading “SNACK!” and large block letters spelling “BUGLES.” The lower panel shows a bowl or circular dish filled with pointed, horn-shaped snacks.\n\nA Bugle is shown in extreme close detail between fingertips. It is a small cone-shaped snack, tapered to a point at one end and open at the other, with a rough, bubbled corn-chip texture. The hand rotates it slowly, first showing the pointed horn shape from the side, then turning it so the hollow circular opening faces forward. A young adult man with short dark hair holds a Bugle near his mouth. He examines it briefly, then bites into it, chews, and smiles slightly, as though enjoying the crunch and flavor.\n\nBugles are then shown with different foods and snack settings. On a tabletop, a white mug sits beside a plate piled with Bugles. A hand lowers a hamburger onto the plate, placing it behind the snacks so the Bugles sit in front as a side snack. Another serving arrangement shows a shallow tray heaped with Bugles, with a small dark glass bottle standing upright behind them; part of the bottle label shows the letters “Co,” suggesting a cola bottle. A hand reaches into the tray and picks up one of the horn-shaped pieces.\n\nNear the end, a Bugles box sits close to the viewer with its top open. Behind it, a young man is partly visible, leaning forward and reaching into the box. The package front clearly reads “SNACK! BUGLES” in bold lettering. The image then returns to the package alone, filling most of the space before pulling back to show the full box against a pale background. The final layout mirrors the earlier Whistles ending: the Bugles package is on the left, and to its right the printed slogan appears again, “suddenly... snacks are in great shape!”",
